Only use the number of bacon pieces you plan to add to your sandwich. Perhaps two or three will do the job. Cook bacon until crispy but not burned. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/2a/Make-a-Waffle-BLT-Step-4Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Waffle-BLT-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/2a/Make-a-Waffle-BLT-Step-4Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Waffle-BLT-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
